   "source": [
    "# Color Spaces\n",
    "color spaces are way to represent the color channels present in image that gives the image a perticular hue."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "a1bd0ff5-2eae-4fcf-acd3-3cc0e0df7cf4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. RGB (Red ,Green ,Blue)\n",
    "2. CMYK (Cyan ,Magenta ,Yellow ,Black) : Unlike RGB ,it is subtractive color space. The CYMK        model works by partially or entirely masking colors on a lighter, usually white, backgraound .\n",
    "\n",
    "3. HSV (Hue , Saturation , Value) : It stores color information in cylinderical representation      of RGB color points.\n",
    "    Hue value varies from 0-179, Saturations value varies from 0-255 and Value valie varies from     0-255."
   ]
  },
